"NON LOCAL USER" PROCEDURES USED IN THE STANDARD ALGORITHM : 
                         TO BE ADAPTED FROM the example user_gurtinSS2nloc3
===================================================================================================


IMPORTANT
---------

   Start from the reference directory amitex_fftp/libAmitex/user_gurtinSS2nloc3

   An example using the corresponding executable is given in amitex_fftp/validation/script_tests.sh

   Developments can be made in any user_directory.  


MAIN IDEAS
----------

   The introduction a new coupling (new physics, new code etc...) with the standard algorithm can 
   be done using the developments made for non-local behaviors


   A FINIR

   

HOWTO : start from user_gurtinSS2nloc3
---------------------------------

Create your own user_directory

      1 / Copy non_local_user_mod.f90, Makefile (and README)
               FROM   amitex_fftp/libAmitex/user_gurtinSS2nloc3 IN   your own user_directory

In your own user_directory

      2 / Adjust the Makefile
               Fill the correct paths lDecomp, lFox, lAmitex, the name of the exutable etc...

      3 / Modify non_local_user_mod.f90 to implement your own model in user_nloc1, user_nloc2 or user_nloc3

      4 / To compile and create a new executable file : make

      5 / To clean :   make clean

